cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper deals with the detection of Denial of Service (DoS) attacks using machine learning classification algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses SNMP-MIB dataset, which is related to network infrastructure, indicating that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another likely category. The use of machine learning algorithms suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with the detection of attacks, which can be considered as a sub-topic of intrusion detection, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category as well.
